CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 1, 1969, pg. 16 reads: "Banquet Committee - Members of the Founder's Day Banquet committee of the alumni chapter of Kappa Alpha Psi are pictured here with principal speaker, Dr. William "Stud" Greene of Washington, D.C. banquet took place at Stouffers Restaurant in Oakland.  Seated from left: Ralph Barnett, chairman; Dr. Greene and George Charlton, Polemarch.  Standing from left: William W. Goode, James Greenlee, Robert W. Smith Jr., Arthur Burt and Henry Tate."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of  Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity members, from left, seated: Ralph Barnett, Dr. William "Stud" Green, and George Charlton; standing: William Goode, James A. Greenlee, Robert W. Smith, Arthur Burt, and Henry Tate, gathered at banquet table in Stouffers Restaurant for Kappa Alpha Psi Founder's Day banquet
